stories.title: Why data needs more than CRUD

stories.text:
Do you have a goto search engine for finding interesting datasets to play with or for benchmarks?

Since I'm mostly interested in it for benchmarking I'm looking for a search engine that lets me search by number of columns and number of rows and sparsity.

Whether or not your favorite engine supports those search criteria I'm still curious to hear what you like.
stories.title: Ask HN: Favorite Dataset Search Engine?

stories.text: I'm reading about data privacy laws in California and I wonder how the blockchain and crypto project play into this. If your data is replicated on n computers around the world, how do you "delete" something?

Tomorrow & Friday a bunch of my coworkers are doing a hackathon. I'm considering launching a simple site to follow along with their progress, and possibly a super basic livestream.

I'm just trying to gauge interest. Would anyone want to follow along or is it a waste of effort?
